<!--==============================================slide=======================================-->
<section data-background="">
					<section>
					
				    <h3><a href="">Better File Management System</a></h3>
				    <ul>
				    	<li>Fragmentation</li>
				    	<li>boot partition: /boot  </li>
				    	<li>system : /</li>
				    	<li>user files : /home</li>
				    	<li>ext2, ext3, ext4, Jfs, Xfs, FAT, FAT32, NTFS</li>				    	
				    </ul>

				    <h3><a href="">No restart except </a></h3>
				    <ul>
				    	<li>After installation of system</li>
				    	<li>Critical updates in system</li>
				    					    	
				    </ul>
				  

				</section>
				</section>


<!--==============================================slide=======================================-->
<section data-background="">
					<section>
					
				    <h3><a href="">Stable</a></h3>
				    <ul>
				    	<li>Linux can run for years without needing to be
restarted (most internet servers run Linux, and they usually never restart).</li>
				    	<li>Linux lets you spend more time working, less time reinstalling and restarting over and over
again.</li>
				    	
				    </ul>
				  

				</section>
				</section>


<!--==============================================slide=======================================-->
<section data-background="#74E2D8">
					<section>
					
				    <h3><a href="">Drivers....?</a></h3>
				    <ul>
				    	<li>Linux doesn't need separate drivers. All the drivers are already included in the
Linux kernel, the core of the system, and that comes with every single Linux
installation.</li>
				    	<li>A very fast and standalone installation process. Once you're done, you have
everything you need to start working (including the software you'll be using).
Out-of-the-box ready peripherals.</li>
				    	
				    </ul>

				  <img src="img/not-found.png">

				</section>
				</section>


